# TP5 — merge via quote-then-replace (see Program.cs ApplyTp5QuoteMergeReplace).
#
# Replaces the old whole-list-rewrite scheme (model re-emits every entry, code checks that
# all-but-one survived character-for-character). That scheme failed live at a ~0-10% success
# rate across two 20-run batches (0/11, 1/13) — asking a 12B model to reproduce N-1 unrelated
# lines byte-for-byte, in the same call where it's also told to rewrite/rephrase things, mostly
# just doesn't hold.
#
# New scheme shrinks the verbatim-fidelity requirement from "every other entry" down to "the one
# entry being replaced": the model quotes that one entry back exactly (grounding technique — see
# Anthropic's own "quote source text before editing" guidance), then writes the merged line. Code
# finds the QUOTE line via exact match against the existing list and splices MERGED in at that
# index; every other entry is preserved by construction, never regenerated by the model at all.
#
# Same char restrictions as tp3_history.gbnf: no leading bullet/digit/asterisk/paren/dash (avoids
# baking list-formatting into stored strings), no "(" ")" "|" (banned commentary / echoed labels).

root ::= "QUOTE:" ws line nl "MERGED:" ws line

ws ::= [ \t]*
nl ::= "\n"
line ::= first-char rest
first-char ::= [^ \t\n*0-9()|-]
rest ::= [^\n()|]*
